<br>
To get to the library one must cross a strange bridge of twisted stone that had been shaped hundreds of years ago by underground streams.  There were no handrails on this bridge, no ropes or nets to protect a person from a bad fall.  It was always rather quiet in this corner of the city, and she saw no one around.  Tzanntiel started to cross the bridge without worry, agile as a cat.<br>
