ed with the hate the conflicts produced. Likewise, the God Rallos Zek, whom Zirrix revered, was pleased that the strong fought against each other and the weakling inferiors were crushed into dust. Each century more and more of the Respected Race were born into the world. In time, perhaps not his lifetime but in time, they would rend everything asunder in hate, death and war. Lifting his head proudly, the aged Warrior saw in his mind’s eye the banner of the Empire and House T’Rhennic, sweeping across flame and carnage filled landscapes. Destroying everything and exterminating all races not born Teir’dal, cleansing the way for the Children of Neriak to fulfill their destiny of vengeance and victory. Looking at the maps, his deep green eyes containing a smoldering fire of anticipation, the General began to think how long it had been since he had been in personal combat. <br>
